                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The feedback obtained by evaluating the aggregated reasoning chain with LLMs may include analysis of limited usefulness and completely incorrect conclusions and error reports. This issue typically arises due to the nature of LLMs, which are language models and do not inherently verify the accuracy of the generated text. Additionally, the capabilities of LLMs, such as gpt- 3.5- turbo, are constrained when used as validators for mathematical problems."
